.SH NAME
HTMLElement.offsetTop \- HTMLElement: offsetTop property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]offsetTop\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R] interface returns the distance from the outer
border of the current element (including its margin) to the top padding
edge of the \f[CR]offsetParent\f[R], the \f[I]closest positioned\f[R]
ancestor element.
.SH VALUE
A number.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] d = document.getElementById(\(dqdiv1\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] topPos = d.offsetTop;

\f[B]if\f[R] (topPos > 10) {
  \f[I]// object offset is more\f[R]
  \f[I]// than 10 pixels from its parent\f[R]
}
.EE
